      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade E46 M3, featuring the iconic S54B32 inline-six power unit with its high-pressure Double VANOS system and individual throttle bodies fully synchronized for optimal volumetric efficiency. This example boasts a reinforced rear subframe and a preemptively refreshed rod bearing set, neutralizing the primary mechanical vulnerabilities of the platform. Power is delivered through a precision Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox to a pristine M Variable Differential Lock. The chassis maintains factory-spec kinematic integrity with zero bushing deflection, while the cross-drilled rotors and OE-spec calipers provide firm, linear deceleration. This specimen is free of oxidation, featuring original paint depth and a cabin devoid of typical bolster wear or plastic delamination.",
